20benefits%20yourself%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226933%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20crowd%20of%20people%20in%20a%20scenic%20city%20street%20walking%20fast%20with%20motion%20blur%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4eb8a9d3b3e45765196bf2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224629%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPick%20up%20the%20pace%20%E2%80%94%20walking%20more%20quickly%20could%20help%20protect%20your%20brain%20and%20body%20from%20age-related%20illnesses.%3Cp%3EMR.Cole_Photographer%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPower%20walking%20could%20be%20the%20key%20to%20a%20long%2C%20healthy%20life%2C%20with%20a%20lower%20risk%20of%20dementia%20and%20disease.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENew%20research%20on%20%26quot%3Bsuper%20movers%26quot%3B%20suggests%20their%20longevity%20secret%20is%20keeping%20a%20brisk%20pace%20after%20age%2080.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20neurologist%20shares%20how%20to%20walk%20your%20way%20to%20antiaging%20benefits%20in%20as%20little%20as%2030%20minutes%20a%20day.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20neurologist%2C%20Dr.%20Joe%20Verghese%20is%20all%20about%20finding%20creative%20strategies%20for%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericas-obsession-paying-to-get-smarter-brain-hacking-adhd-alzheimers-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehealthier%20brain%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20when%20it%20helps%20simplify%20his%20workout%20routine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20always%20enjoy%20exercising%2C%20or%20the%20idea%20that%20I%20have%20to%20do%20it%20regularly%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20pursuit%20of%20a%20healthier%20brain%2C%20he's%20tried%20everything%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbalance-test-linked-to-longevity-health-study-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebalance%20tests%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20ballroom%20dancing%20(after%20his%20studies%20found%20it%20may%20help%20stave%20off%20dementia).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20the%20Stony%20Brook%20University%20researcher%20is%20aiming%20to%20become%20a%20%26quot%3Bsuper%20mover%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20rare%20demographic%20of%20people%2080%20and%20older%20who%20have%20an%20exceptionally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbrisk-walking-slow-signs-aging-16-years-study-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efast%20walking%20speed%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20their%20age%20%E2%80%94%20and%20live%20uniquely%20long%2C%20healthy%20lives%3Cs%3E.%3C%2Fs%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20his%20studies%2C%20persistent%20speediness%20may%20have%20a%20protective%20effect%20on%20the%20brain%20and%20body%2C%20Verghese%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20studying%20them%2C%20he%20hopes%20to%20learn%20not%20just%20how%20our%20bodies%20and%20minds%20deteriorate%20as%20we%20age%2C%20but%20what%20we%20can%20do%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAspiring%20to%20be%20a%20fast%20mover%2C%20a%20super%20mover%20is%20a%20good%20thing%20because%20it%20has%20not%20only%20benefits%20for%20the%20brain%2C%20it%20has%20benefits%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20body%20too%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2295950d33-abb8-46fd-bd78-c722449d1364%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMove%20fast%2C%20slow%20aging%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESuper%20movers%20are%20defined%20as%20people%20who%20can%20keep%20pace%20with%20someone%20decades%20younger%2C%20like%20an%2080-year-old%20walking%20at%20the%20speed%20of%20an%20average%2050-year-old%2C%20Verghese%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20most%20recent%20study%2C%20published%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.neurology.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1212%2FWNL.0000000000214776%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejournal%20Neurology%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20found%20that%20super%20movers%20are%2050%25%20less%20likely%20to%20develop%20cognitive%20impairment%20than%20their%20peers.%20Another%20of%20his%20studies%20found%20that%20super%20movers%20had%20a%20younger%20biological%20age%20than%20their%20years%20would%20suggest%2C%20and%20lower%20rates%20of%20heart%20disease%2C%20depression%20symptoms%2C%20and%20hearing%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbrisk-walking-reverse-brain-aging-in-older-adults-study-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBrisk%20walking%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20long%20been%20linked%20to%20longevity%2C%20so%20that%20wasn't%20a%20surprise.%20What%20was%20intriguing%2C%20Verghese%20said%2C%20were%20the%20autopsy%20results%20of%20people%20who%20died%20during%20the%20study.%20After%20death%2C%20super%20movers%20were%20just%20as%20likely%20to%20show%20age-related%20wear%20and%20tear%20in%20their%20brain%20tissue%20as%20their%20slower-walking%20peers.%20On%20average%2C%20though%2C%20they%20showed%20fewer%20symptoms%20of%20cognitive%20decline%20during%20their%20lifetimes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227360%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22two%20elderly%20couples%20walking%20outside%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4fbaa4d3a449ec3445fb7e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224912%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESuper%20movers%20who%20keep%20walking%20fast%20in%20their%2080s%20and%20beyond%20have%20better%20memory%2C%20mood%2C%20and%20cognitive%20health%2C%20research%20suggests.%3Cp%3ESeventyFour%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EVerghese%20was%20inspired%20to%20seek%20out%20super%20movers%20based%20on%20previous%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flongevity-doctor-superagers-shares-anti-aging-secrets-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eresearch%20on%20super-agers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20people%20who%20retain%20the%20physical%20and%20mental%20spryness%20of%20someone%20much%20younger%2C%20in%20part%20because%20of%20lucky%20genetics.%20And%20as%20with%20super%20movers%2C%20studies%20on%20super-agers'%20brains%20have%20similar%20rates%20of%20deterioration%20on%20average%2C%20with%20fewer%20symptoms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20only%2019%25%20of%20super%20movers%20are%20also%20super-agers.%20That%20suggests%20there%20may%20be%20multiple%20strategies%20to%20protect%20your%20brain%20from%20aging%2C%20Verghese%20said.%20More%20research%20could%20help%20provide%20personalized%20recommendations%20for%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-boost-longevity-4-minutes-daily-exercise-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eantiaging%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20might%20have%20some%20unique%20resilience%20mechanisms%20that%20might%20prevent%20you%20from%20showing%20those%20effects%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228b762ea3-6da7-41db-837a-df000c8d5a9e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EPower%20walking%20for%20a%20healthy%20brain%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20importantly%2C%20you%20may%20not%20need%20to%20win%20the%20genetic%20lottery%20to%20be%20a%20super%20mover.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVerghese%20found%20evidence%20that%20super%20movers%20were%20speedy%20before%20they%20reached%20age%2080.%20While%20genetics%20likely%20play%20a%20role%2C%20getting%20comfortable%20with%20a%20brisk%20walking%20pace%20now%20will%20make%20you%20more%20likely%20to%20maintain%20it%20and%20become%20a%20super%20mover%20later%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20walk%20your%20way%20to%20longevity%2C%20your%20pace%20should%20be%20around%203%20miles%20per%20hour%2C%20studies%20suggest%2C%20and%20faster%20may%20be%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAim%20for%20at%20least%2030%20minutes%20a%20day%2C%20in%20line%20with%20the%20CDC's%20recommended%20150-300%20minutes%20of%20moderate%20activity%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20have%20to%20do%20the%2030%20minutes%20in%20one%20go.%20You%20can%20split%20it%20up.%2010%20minutes%20is%20better%20than%20zero%20minutes%2C%26quot%3B%20Verghese%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsuper-mover-live-longer-protect-brain-neurologist-how-to-tips-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1783772161000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4fb891d3a449ec3445fb69%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsuper-mover-live-longer-protect-brain-neurologist-how-to-tips-2026-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20best%20longevity%20secret%20may%20be%20a%20power%20walk.%20A%20neurologist%20explains%20how%20moving%20fast%20helps%20protect%20the%20brain%20and%20body%20from%20aging.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22glandsverk%40insider.com%20(Gabby%20Landsverk)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A89%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22After%20living%20with%20my%20parents%20for%206%20years%2C%20we're%20now%20neighbors.%20We%20have%20plenty%20of%20the%20benefits%20of%20living%20together%2C%20but%20more%20privacy.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222165%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22the%20author%20with%20her%20mom%20and%20a%20cake%20that%20says%20%26quot%3Bcongrats%20sam%26quot%3B%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4d325f965805a2c542dab2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222887%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author's%20mom%20surprised%20her%20with%20a%20cake%20when%20her%20book%20cover%20was%20revealed.%20She%20says%20that%20being%20able%20to%20stop%20by%20their%20house%20for%20a%20quick%20meal%20or%20a%20TV%20show%20has%20become%20essential%20during%20a%20year%20filled%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20work%20and%20little%20free%20time.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Samantha%20Paige%20Rosen%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EI%20lived%20with%20my%20parents%20for%20six%20years%2C%20until%20they%20decided%20to%20retire%20and%20downsize%20a%20year%20ago.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI%20loved%20living%20with%20them%20and%20decided%20to%20move%20in%20across%20the%20street%20from%20their%20townhouse.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThis%20year%20was%20hectic%2C%20and%20the%20quality%20time%2C%20shared%20grocery%20costs%2C%20and%20pet%20day%20care%20were%20so%20helpful.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-moved-in-with-parents-multigenerational-living-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emoved%20in%20with%20my%20parents%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20my%20late%2020s%2C%20I%20did%20not%20expect%20the%20arrangement%20to%20carry%20me%20into%20my%20mid-30s.%20I%20stayed%20because%2C%20although%20it%20was%20different%20from%20what%20anyone%20in%20my%20social%20circle%20was%20doing%2C%20I%20was%20surprised%20by%20how%20much%20we%20all%20enjoyed%20it.%20In%20this%20house%20of%20three%20adults%20who%20cared%20deeply%20about%20one%20another's%20well-being%2C%20my%20life%20was%20better%20than%20it%20had%20been%20in%20a%20while.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20part%2C%20for%20me%2C%20was%20the%20interdependence%20%E2%80%94%20coming%20off%20of%20two%20years%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-into-first-apartment-alone-challenges-rewarding-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eliving%20by%20myself%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20even%20being%20able%20to%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BCould%20you%20make%20me%20a%20sandwich%2C%20too%3F%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BNo%20problem%2C%20I'll%20get%20your%20headache%20meds%20from%20upstairs!%26quot%3B%20felt%20refreshing.%20I%20also%20appreciated%20the%20opportunity%20for%20unscheduled%20quality%20time%20and%20the%20sense%20that%20I%20was%20never%20completely%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20felt%20like%20I'd%20uncovered%20a%20secret%2C%20and%20I%20wondered%20what%20other%20iterations%20of%20housing%20and%20community%20I'd%20been%20missing%20out%20on.%20I%20decided%20to%20edit%20an%20anthology%20on%20the%20subject%2C%20which%20became%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3Fh%3D5a3ca26db80f625cf80aa29dc990c4e6cbeca67e894f55f0df6077002e02d25b%26postID%3D6a4d306cf38dd8af49600e54%26postSlug%3Dlived-with-parents-adult-now-neighbors-benefits-2026-7%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fbookshop.org%252Fa%252F120570%252F9780807021293%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELiving%2C%20Together%3A%20Reimagining%20Community%20in%20the%20Age%20of%20Disconnection%3C%2Fa%3E.%20When%20my%20parents%20wanted%20to%20retire%20and%20downsize%20after%20six%20years%20of%2C%20well%2C%20living%20together%2C%20and%20I%20had%20to%20look%20for%20my%20own%20place%20again%2C%20I%20kept%20everything%20I%20learned%20from%20the%20book's%20stories%20in%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoving%20out%20of%20my%20parents'%20house%2C%20I%20imagined%20I'd%20settle%20in%20a%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fliving-in-walkable-neighborhood-could-help-you-live-100-study-2020-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewalkable%20neighborhood%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20the%20one%20they%20chose.%20When%20a%20townhouse%20opened%20up%20across%20the%20parking%20lot%20from%20theirs%2C%20I%20was%20reluctant%20to%20look%20at%20it.%20Surely%20I%20couldn't%20go%20from%20living%20with%20my%20parents%20in%20my%2030s%20to%20living%20mere%20steps%20away.%20But%20the%20more%20I%20thought%20about%20it%2C%20the%20more%20I%20liked%20the%20prospect%20of%20continuing%20the%20casual%20hangs%2C%20resource%20sharing%2C%20and%20emotional%20support%20that%20have%20enriched%20our%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20been%20almost%20a%20year%20since%20we%20became%20neighbors%2C%20and%20I%20think%20it%20was%20a%20great%20move.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221576%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20townhouse%20and%20cars%20in%20a%20parking%20lot%2C%20with%20a%20red%20circle%20outlining%20a%20man%20walking%20by%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4d32d294175b768171fb1e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221182%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELast%20year%2C%20the%20author%20moved%20to%20a%20townhouse%20across%20the%20parking%20lot%20from%20her%20parents.%20This%20picture%20shows%20the%20distance%20from%20their%20house%20to%20her%20balcony%20%E2%80%94%20her%20dad%20is%20in%20the%20red%20circle%2C%20she%20asked%20him%20to%20stop%20for%20a%20photo%20when%20he%20was%20walking%20by.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Samantha%20Paige%20Rosen%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225a1d495e-b5f8-48f2-aad9-56ae0e562813%5C%22%3EWe%20have%20more%20privacy%20and%20flexibility%20than%20when%20we%20lived%20together%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmultigenerational-living-with-parents-financial-relief-adult-identity-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elived%20with%20my%20parents%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20was%20sometimes%20difficult%20for%20them%20because%20I%20needed%20quiet%20while%20working.%20Now%2C%20I%20can%20have%20that%20at%20my%20house%2C%20and%20my%20parents%20don't%20have%20to%20worry%20about%20the%20volume%20of%20their%20TV%20shows%20or%20phone%20calls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20don't%20typically%20stop%20by%20one%20another's%20houses%20constantly%20and%20unannounced%2C%20even%20though%20we%20live%20so%20close%20and%20have%20each%20other's%20house%20keys.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223a4168df-88e8-4f4a-87c6-e206b2aa34db%5C%22%3EI%20avoid%20the%20single-person%20grocery%20curse%2C%20and%20they%20save%20money%20by%20sharing%2C%20too%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bane%20of%20my%20existence%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-live-alone-status-symbol-rents-housing-homeownership-expensive-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esingle%20person%20living%20alone%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20food%20that%20rots%20in%20the%20fridge.%20Lunch%20meat%2C%20melon%2C%20fresh%20mozzarella%20%E2%80%94%20I%20somehow%20can%20never%20eat%20it%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20first%20time%20I've%20lived%20alone%20and%20been%20able%20to%20share%20groceries%20because%20my%20parents%20live%20so%20close%20by.%20It%20ensures%20food%20and%20money