i%3EAkil%20manages%20travel%20expenses%20by%20using%20platforms%20like%20Airbnb%20and%20spends%20%242%2C000%20a%20month%20on%20housing.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAfter%20his%20tour%2C%20Akil%20found%20international%20living%20offered%20a%20better%20quality%20of%20life%20than%20in%20the%20U.S.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Bakari%20Akil%2C%2037%2C%20a%20private%20equity%20investor%20from%20New%20York.%20Akil%20grew%20up%20with%20no%20international%20travel%20experience%20and%2C%20three%20years%20ago%2C%20set%20out%20to%20visit%2030%20different%20countries%20each%20month.%20He%20finished%20his%20list%2C%20but%20is%20still%20traveling%20around%20the%20world.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20I%20knew%20were%20traveling%20around%20and%20out%20of%20the%20country%2C%20and%20doing%20all%20this%20really%20cool%20stuff%2C%20and%20I%20was%20just%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BHow%20are%20people%20pulling%20this%20off%3F%26quot%3B%20I%20just%20couldn't%20figure%20out%20how%20people%20were%20living%20these%20cool%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I%20was%20at%20the%20Equinox%20on%2067th%20Street%20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%20one%20of%20my%20gym%20friends%20had%20just%20come%20back%20from%20a%20trip%20internationally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BYo%2C%20how%20do%20you%20travel%20like%20that%3F%26quot%3B%20He%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI've%20been%20doing%20this%20since%20I%20was%20a%20kid.%26quot%3B%20I%20didn't%20have%20any%20international%20traveling%20under%20my%20belt%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20me%20to%20look%20into%20this%20program%20called%20Remote%20Year.%20I%20looked%20it%20up.%20The%20program%20takes%20other%20digital%20nomads%2C%20people%20who%20don't%20have%20to%20be%20locked%20into%20whatever%20location%2C%20on%20month-long%20trips.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERemote%20Year%20would%20find%20your%20housing%2C%20they'd%20find%20stuff%20for%20you%20to%20do%20inside%20the%20country%2C%20and%20they'd%20introduce%20you%20to%20people%20who%20were%20there.%20They%20even%20covered%20the%20flights%20between%20the%20countries%20as%20you%20were%20going%20to%20the%20next%20country.%20The%20only%20thing%20they%20didn't%20cover%20was%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20smiling%20person%20in%20black%20clothing%20poses%20in%20front%20of%20the%20Taj%20Mahal%20on%20a%20misty%20day.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4ffec2d3b3e4576519730d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAkil%20in%20front%20of%20the%20Taj%20Mahal.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Bakari%20Akil%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20all-inclusive%20in%20a%20monthly%20%242%2C000%20fee.%20I%20was%20paying%20about%20%243%2C000%20a%20month%20to%20live%20in%20New%20York%20City%20just%20for%20rent%20%E2%80%94%20not%20including%20the%20gym%20and%20all%20that%20other%20stuff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey're%20saying%20I%20can%20go%20live%20in%20a%20different%20country%20every%20month%20for%2060%25%20of%20what%20I'm%20paying%20for%20rent%3F%20What%20am%20I%20doing%2C%20of%20course%20I%20should%20do%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20learned%20about%20it%20in%20March%202023%2C%20and%20I%20was%20on%20the%20trip%20with%20them%20by%20July.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227a4a6671-9035-4c73-bdf4-710b2a5b7e9f%5C%22%3EI%20had%20a%20strict%20list%20of%2030%20countries%20I%20wanted%20to%20visit%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20on%20a%20plane%2C%20and%20I%20flew%20to%20Cape%20Town%2C%20South%20Africa.%20I%20traveled%20with%20Remote%20Year%20for%20four%20months.%20We%20went%20to%20South%20Africa%2C%20Greece%2C%20Spain%2C%20and%20Turkey%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20in%20Turkey%2C%20I%20left%20them.%20Since%20then%2C%20I%20have%20basically%20lived%20in%20a%20different%20country%20every%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20went%20to%20India%2C%20then%20Thailand%2C%20then%20Vietnam%2C%20all%20throughout%20Southeast%20Asia.%20Then%20I%20went%20to%20East%20Asia%3A%20China%2C%20Japan%2C%20and%20Korea.%20I%20went%20to%20Jamaica%2C%20and%20then%20I%20flew%20to%20Ghana%2C%20Nigeria%2C%20Kenya%2C%20Ethiopia%2C%20and%20Egypt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Person%20reclines%20on%20a%20sofa%20in%20a%20modern%20hotel%20room%20with%20a%20bed%2C%20city%20view%2C%20and%20SAIGON%20wall%20art.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4ffec2b3a8c16f7e8ed178%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAkil%20enjoying%20his%20room%20in%20Vietnam.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Bakari%20Akil%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20I%20spent%20a%20month%20in%20Israel%20and%20Palestine%2C%20going%20back%20and%20forth%20between%20Tel%20Aviv%20and%20Ramallah.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20did%20a%20European%20tour%20last%20summer.%20I%20was%20in%20Berlin%2C%20and%20then%20I%20spent%20a%20month%20in%20London%2C%20Paris%2C%20and%20Rome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Rome%2C%20I%20went%20to%20South%20America%20for%20the%20first%20time.%20I%20went%20to%20Peru.%20And%20then%20I%20went%20up%20to%20Mexico.%20I%20spent%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20time%20in%20the%20Caribbean%20in%20Cuba%2C%20the%20Dominican%20Republic%2C%20and%20Puerto%20Rico.%20Then%20from%20Puerto%20Rico%2C%20I%20flew%20to%20Colombia%2C%20Brazil%2C%20and%20Argentina%20in%20March%20of%20this%20year%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20when%20I%20officially%20wrapped%20up%20my%20specific%20tour%20of%2030%20countries%20I'd%20wanted%20to%20go%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20people%20got%20a%20chance%20to%20study%20abroad%20%E2%80%94%20I%20didn't%20get%20a%20chance%20to%20do%20that.%20So%20this%20was%20me%20catching%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c1ed80a6-3a87-4f68-8236-85354f1369d4%5C%22%3EI%20tried%20to%20keep%20my%20expenses%20consistent%20across%20countries%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etravel%20expenses%20between%20the%20nations%20were%20a%20couple%20of%20hundred%20dollars.%20If%20I'm%20flying%20from%20America%20to%20Thailand%2C%20it's%20going%20to%20cost%20me%20maybe%20%241%2C000.%20But%20if%20I'm%20flying%20from%20Cambodia%20to%20Thailand%2C%20it%20might%20cost%20me%20%24100.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20was%3A%20while%20I'm%20right%20next%20to%20places%2C%20go%20visit%20them%20and%20make%20it%20easier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221875%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Person%20standing%20on%20a%20balcony%20near%20the%20Colosseum%20under%20a%20bright%20blue%20sky.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4ffec2d3a449ec3445fedc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAkil%20in%20front%20of%20the%20Colosseum%20in%20Rome.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Bakari%20Akil%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Asia%2C%20Africa%2C%20South%20America%2C%20and%20parts%20of%20the%20Caribbean%2C%20it%20would%20be%20very%20difficult%20or%20very%20unlikely%20for%20me%20to%20spend%20more%20than%20%242%2C000%20a%20month%20on%20housing.%20The%20platforms%20I%20would%20use%20primarily%20were%20Airbnb%20and%20Booking.com.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAirbnb%20has%20always%20been%20the%20best%20for%20me%20because%20I%20want%20to%20cook%2C%20and%20it's%20not%20impossible%2C%20but%20it's%20harder%20to%20find%20hotels%20outside%20Asia%20that%20will%20provide%20you%20with%20a%20room%20that%20also%20has%20a%20kitchen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20each%20place%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI'm%20staying%20for%20a%20month%2C%20and%20I'm%20spending%20about%20%242%2C000%20to%20live%2C%20and%20not%20in%20a%20faraway%20area%20%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%94%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ein%20the%20same%20kind%20of%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebuilding%20that%20I%20was%20aspiring%20to%20live%20in%20when%20I%20was%20living%20in%20New%20York.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20in%20South%20Africa%2C%20I%20was%20living%20in%20the%20Victoria%20and%20Alfred%20area%2C%20which%20is%20the%20most%20expensive%20area%20in%20all%20of%20Cape%20Town%2C%20and%20I%20paid%20less%20than%20%242%2C000%20for%20the%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20cool%20thing%20is%20that%2C%20unlike%20rent%2C%20when%20I'm%20in%20London%20for%20a%20month%2C%20and%20I%20know%20I'm%20going%20to%20be%20spending%2012%20months%20abroad%2C%20one%20month%20might%20be%20%242%2C800%2C%20and%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20next%20might%20be%20%241%2C400.%20It%20ends%20up%20balancing%20itself%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20before%20I%20left%20on%20my%20trip%20in%202023%2C%20I%20also%20applied%20for%20dual%20citizenship%20(I'm%20Jamaican%20by%20lineage).%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20got%20my%20Jamaican%20and%20American%20passports%2C%20which%20made%20it%20easy%20for%20me%20to%20navigate%20throughout%20Africa%20because%20there%20are%20certain%20nations%20where%2C%20if%20you%20bring%20your%20Jamaican%20passport%2C%20you%20don't%20have%20to%20pay%20a%20visa%20fee%2C%20or%20you%20can%20pay%20a%20lower%20visa%20fee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20with%20a%20Jamaican%20passport%2C%20Ghana%20is%20visa-free%2C%20and%20Nigeria%20is%20cheaper%20than%20a%20United%20States%20visa.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c1e26cb6-ffe5-436d-a50d-653918c10814%5C%22%3EI%20wanted%20to%20travel%20the%20US%2C%20too%2C%20but%20it's%20so%20expensive%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20I%20finished%20my%20initial%20trip%20in%20March%2C%20I%20came%20back%20to%20the%20US%20for%20a%20month.%20I%20spent%20a%20month%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20and%20was%20excited%20to%20come%20back%20to%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20I%20was%20thinking%20I%20was%20going%20to%20do%20the%20same%20thing%20I%20had%20done%20internationally.%20I'll%20spend%20a%20month%20in%20Washington%2C%20then%20a%20month%20in%20Boston%2C%20then%20Chicago%2C%20and%20New%20York%2C%20and%20get%20a%20good%20sense%20of%20my%20home%20country.%20I'd%20been%20international%2C%20and%20I%20hadn't%20done%20the%20same%20thing%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20smiling%20person%20seated%20outdoors%20in%20front%20of%20the%20El%20Castillo%20pyramid%20at%20Chich%C3%A9n%20Itz%C3%A1%20under%20a%20clear%20blue%20sky.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4ffec2d3b3e4576519730e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221803%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAkil%20in%20front%20of%20a%20pyramid%20in%20Chich%C3%A9n%20Itz%C3%A1.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Bakari%20Akil%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20time%20I%20went%20grocery%20shopping%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20I%20was%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20is%20going%20on%3F%20Why%20is%20it%20so%20expensive%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%2C%20you%20go%20inside%20a%20grocery%20store%2C%20you%20spend%20%2450%2C%20and%20you%20have%20a%20very%20well-stocked%20fridge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20coming%20from%20Argentina.%20I%20go%20back%20to%20the%20capital%20of%20my%20country%2C%20and%20it's%20just%20like%2C%20wow.%20It's%20unaffordable%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I'm%20not%20poor.%20It%20felt%20like%20the%20quality%20of%20life%20outside%20the%20United%20States%20was%20better%20than%20inside%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223d09d8ac-3359-4a87-9744-b15bdeefb833%5C%22%3EI'm%20looking%20for%20somewhere%20to%20stay%20longer%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20coming%20back%20home%2C%20I%20feel%20like%20I'm%20an%20international%20guy%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20in%20Bangkok%20now.%20But%20now%20I%20am%20thinking%2C%20%26quot%3BWhere%20are%20those%20places%20I%20can%20stay%20permanently%3F%26quot%3B%20Mexico%20City's%20one%20of%20those%2C%20Bangkok%20is%20one%20of%20them%2C%20Nairobi%2C%20Cape%20Town%2C%20and%20a%20few%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20am%20a%20very%20big%20proponent%20of%20ownership%2C%20but%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI've%20always%20felt%20like%20the%20idea%20of%20owning%20your%20own%20home%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20owning%20a%3Cs%3E%20%3C%2Fs%3Ehome%20felt%20like%20a%20vanity%20thing%20%E2%80%94%20not%20necessarily%20a%20great%20financial%20situation.%20People%20end%20up%20spending%20way%20more%20than%20what%20they%20intended%20to%20spend%20when%20they%20buy%20their%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20flexibility%20to%20wake%20up%20and%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BAll%20right%2C%20Bangkok%20was%20nice.%20Now%20let's%20go%20to%20X%2C%20Y%2C%20Z%2C%26quot%3B%20is%20impossible%20if%20I%20own%20a%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleft-nyc-lived-30-countries-cheaper-than-rent-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1783771261000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4ffec2d3a449ec3445fedd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleft-nyc-lived-30-countries-cheaper-than-rent-2026-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Bakari%20Akil%20shares%20his%20experience%20traveling%20to%20a%20new%20country%20each%20month%20while%20still%20spending%20less%20than%20his%20rent%20in%20New%20York.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jpandy%40insider.com%20(Jordan%20Pandy)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I'm%20a%20single%20mom%2C%20living%20in%20the%20Hamptons.%20It's%20a%20struggle%20to%20pay%20my%20%244%2C000%20rent%20and%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20glamorous%20lifestyle.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221242%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Vanessa%20Gordon%20and%20her%20daughter%20smiling%20to%20camera%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4695231bba93485607ade0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22932%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20is%20raising%20her%20two%20children%20in%20the%20Hamptons.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Vanessa%20Gordon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EI'm%20raising%20my%20kids%20in%20the%20Hamptons%20as%20a%20single%20mom%2C%20and%20it%20isn't%2